rocess of self-experimentation. He follows Davy from his youthful enthusiasm for physiological experiment through his self-fashioning as a man of science in a period when the path to a scientific career was not as well-trodden as it is today. What emerges is a portrait of Davy as a creative fashioner of his own identity through a lifelong series of experiments in selfhood.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aChemistszEnglandvBiography. 0aDavy, Humphry. 0aScientistszEnglandvBiography. 7aSCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  ahumphry davy, baronet, cornish, chemist, chemistry, science, invention, inventor, scientist, lamp, electricity, electrochemistry, physical, electrical potential, chemical change, history, humanities, historical, 19th century, royal society, self experimentation, identity, selfhood, england, english, biography, education, scientific interests, herculaneum papyri, president, understanding, presentation.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311071098440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226368849423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226368849/original  a978-3-11-071098-4  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles